<paragraph blockId="1.[575,686,414,438]" box="[575,686,414,438]" pageId="1" pageNumber="72">
(
<figureCitation box="[582,676,414,438]" captionStart="Figs 1–8" captionStartId="2.[100,137,1620,1639]" captionTargetBox="[108,1124,191,1590]" captionTargetId="figure-10@2.[108,623,191,932]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1–8. Hippaphora viklundi sp. nov. female. 1 – dorsal view; 2 – dorsal view of head; 3 – ventral view of head; 4 – postpedicel; 5 – eye; 6 – wing plus haltere (h); 7 – hairs of dorsal face of abdomen; 8 – hind femora." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6251802" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6251802/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="72">Figs 1–8</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[100,1121,460,699]" pageId="1" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[140,223,460,484]" pageId="1" pageNumber="72">Female</emphasis>
. 
<figureCitation box="[239,304,460,484]" captionStart="Figs 1–8" captionStartId="2.[100,137,1620,1639]" captionTargetBox="[108,1124,191,1590]" captionTargetId="figure-10@2.[108,623,191,932]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1–8. Hippaphora viklundi sp. nov. female. 1 – dorsal view; 2 – dorsal view of head; 3 – ventral view of head; 4 – postpedicel; 5 – eye; 6 – wing plus haltere (h); 7 – hairs of dorsal face of abdomen; 8 – hind femora." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6251802" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6251802/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="72">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
depicts the whole fly from above. The head enlarged as 
<figureCitation box="[946,1011,460,484]" captionStart="Figs 1–8" captionStartId="2.[100,137,1620,1639]" captionTargetBox="[108,1124,191,1590]" captionTargetId="figure-10@2.[108,623,191,932]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1–8. Hippaphora viklundi sp. nov. female. 1 – dorsal view; 2 – dorsal view of head; 3 – ventral view of head; 4 – postpedicel; 5 – eye; 6 – wing plus haltere (h); 7 – hairs of dorsal face of abdomen; 8 – hind femora." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6251802" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6251802/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="72">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
and from below as in 
<figureCitation box="[231,297,491,515]" captionStart="Figs 1–8" captionStartId="2.[100,137,1620,1639]" captionTargetBox="[108,1124,191,1590]" captionTargetId="figure-10@2.[108,623,191,932]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1–8. Hippaphora viklundi sp. nov. female. 1 – dorsal view; 2 – dorsal view of head; 3 – ventral view of head; 4 – postpedicel; 5 – eye; 6 – wing plus haltere (h); 7 – hairs of dorsal face of abdomen; 8 – hind femora." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6251802" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6251802/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="72">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
. The postpedicels as in 
<figureCitation box="[554,619,491,515]" captionStart="Figs 1–8" captionStartId="2.[100,137,1620,1639]" captionTargetBox="[108,1124,191,1590]" captionTargetId="figure-10@2.[108,623,191,932]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1–8. Hippaphora viklundi sp. nov. female. 1 – dorsal view; 2 – dorsal view of head; 3 – ventral view of head; 4 – postpedicel; 5 – eye; 6 – wing plus haltere (h); 7 – hairs of dorsal face of abdomen; 8 – hind femora." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6251802" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6251802/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="72">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
. The eyes are reduced to just a few ommatidia (
<figureCitation box="[108,177,521,546]" captionStart="Figs 1–8" captionStartId="2.[100,137,1620,1639]" captionTargetBox="[108,1124,191,1590]" captionTargetId="figure-10@2.[108,623,191,932]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1–8. Hippaphora viklundi sp. nov. female. 1 – dorsal view; 2 – dorsal view of head; 3 – ventral view of head; 4 – postpedicel; 5 – eye; 6 – wing plus haltere (h); 7 – hairs of dorsal face of abdomen; 8 – hind femora." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6251802" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6251802/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="72">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Thorax with fine hairs, an intra-alar bristle, 3 notopleural bristles, 3 bristles on the reduced mesopleuron and some bristles on propleuron. Wing and haltere as in 
<figureCitation box="[995,1064,552,576]" captionStart="Figs 1–8" captionStartId="2.[100,137,1620,1639]" captionTargetBox="[108,1124,191,1590]" captionTargetId="figure-10@2.[108,623,191,932]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1–8. Hippaphora viklundi sp. nov. female. 1 – dorsal view; 2 – dorsal view of head; 3 – ventral view of head; 4 – postpedicel; 5 – eye; 6 – wing plus haltere (h); 7 – hairs of dorsal face of abdomen; 8 – hind femora." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6251802" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6251802/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="72">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
. The abdominal hairs are fine (
<figureCitation box="[374,439,583,607]" captionStart="Figs 1–8" captionStartId="2.[100,137,1620,1639]" captionTargetBox="[108,1124,191,1590]" captionTargetId="figure-10@2.[108,623,191,932]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1–8. Hippaphora viklundi sp. nov. female. 1 – dorsal view; 2 – dorsal view of head; 3 – ventral view of head; 4 – postpedicel; 5 – eye; 6 – wing plus haltere (h); 7 – hairs of dorsal face of abdomen; 8 – hind femora." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6251802" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6251802/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="72">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). The hind femora as in 
<figureCitation box="[700,765,583,607]" captionStart="Figs 1–8" captionStartId="2.[100,137,1620,1639]" captionTargetBox="[108,1124,191,1590]" captionTargetId="figure-10@2.[108,623,191,932]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1–8. Hippaphora viklundi sp. nov. female. 1 – dorsal view; 2 – dorsal view of head; 3 – ventral view of head; 4 – postpedicel; 5 – eye; 6 – wing plus haltere (h); 7 – hairs of dorsal face of abdomen; 8 – hind femora." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6251802" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6251802/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="72">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
